text: Newly open. Cai fan stall had a good variety of options. When you look at the spread, it will already whet your appetite by the looks of how it’s cooked. Ladies fingers, steam egg and curry chicken were on point! Will eat again.

Travelled an hour to repair my luggage in a nearby industrial building and came across this food court to have breakfast!
Staff were friendly and they smile ☺️
(But possibly coz i didn’t come during rush hour , idk how its like when its busy here)
Bought teh peng from kopimaster ($2) • tasted alright
Caifan - curry chicken, fried egg and bee hoon ($3.40, not bad) • Chicken and potato were tender
Nice place clean order cup of coffee black taste good but $1.40 is high though. Newly renovated.
